&lt;h4 id=&#34;23-external-resources-are-required-for-a-program-the-program-manager-receives-bids-from-multiple-vendors-and-presents-the-top-vendor-to-the-program-governance-board-one-program-governance-board-member-asks-the-program-manager-to-select-a-vendor-that-was-dismissed-early-in-the-selection-process-because-they-were-not-on-the-approved-vendor-list-the-program-manager-learns-that-this-program-governance-board-member-has-a-personal-connection-to-this-vendor-what-should-the-program-manager-do&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#23-external-resources-are-required-for-a-program-the-program-manager-receives-bids-from-multiple-vendors-and-presents-the-top-vendor-to-the-program-governance-board-one-program-governance-board-member-asks-the-program-manager-to-select-a-vendor-that-was-dismissed-early-in-the-selection-process-because-they-were-not-on-the-approved-vendor-list-the-program-manager-learns-that-this-program-governance-board-member-has-a-personal-connection-to-this-vendor-what-should-the-program-manager-do&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 23. External resources are required for a program. The program manager receives bids from multiple vendors and presents the top vendor to the program governance board. One program governance board member asks the program manager to select a vendor that was dismissed early in the selection process because they were not on the approved vendor list. The program manager learns that this program governance board member has a personal connection to this vendor. What should the program manager do?&lt;/h4&gt;
