&lt;h4 id=&#34;168-an-organization-must-accelerate-a-product-to-market-the-program-manager-completes-the-preliminary-program-steps-and-holds-a-kick-off-meeting-project-managers-submit-their-preliminary-schedules-for-review-what-should-the-program-manager-do-next&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#168-an-organization-must-accelerate-a-product-to-market-the-program-manager-completes-the-preliminary-program-steps-and-holds-a-kick-off-meeting-project-managers-submit-their-preliminary-schedules-for-review-what-should-the-program-manager-do-next&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 168. An organization must accelerate a product to market. The program manager completes the preliminary program steps and holds a kick-off meeting. Project managers submit their preliminary schedules for review. What should the program manager do next?&lt;/h4&gt;
