 C. 收益是量化的，以便降低风险&lt;br /&gt;
 D. 收益是量化的，以便随着时间的推移度量收益的实现情况&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;57-a-program-manager-who-reports-to-a-companys-cio-is-responsible-for-managing-a-strategic-initiative-program-during-a-program-review-meeting-the-cio-informs-the-program-manager-about-potential-budget-cuts-that-would-impact-program-resources-and-urges-the-program-manager-to-begin-delivering-benefits-more-quickly-to-continue-the-program-what-should-the-program-manager-do-first&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#57-a-program-manager-who-reports-to-a-companys-cio-is-responsible-for-managing-a-strategic-initiative-program-during-a-program-review-meeting-the-cio-informs-the-program-manager-about-potential-budget-cuts-that-would-impact-program-resources-and-urges-the-program-manager-to-begin-delivering-benefits-more-quickly-to-continue-the-program-what-should-the-program-manager-do-first&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 57. A program manager, who reports to a company’s CIO, is responsible for managing a strategic initiative program. During a program review meeting, the CIO informs the program manager about potential budget cuts that would impact program resources, and urges the program manager to begin delivering benefits more quickly to continue the program. What should the program manager do first?&lt;/h4&gt;
