&lt;h4 id=&#34;78-the-program-manager-has-a-global-program-with-five-component-projects-the-program-sponsor-wants-the-management-plans-processesprocedures-and-technology-to-be-uniform-across-the-program-the-requirements-will-create-issues-and-result-in-increased-costs-the-program-sponsor-is-new-and-has-imposed-these-new-requirements-six-months-into-a-three-year-program-what-should-the-program-manager-do-next&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#78-the-program-manager-has-a-global-program-with-five-component-projects-the-program-sponsor-wants-the-management-plans-processesprocedures-and-technology-to-be-uniform-across-the-program-the-requirements-will-create-issues-and-result-in-increased-costs-the-program-sponsor-is-new-and-has-imposed-these-new-requirements-six-months-into-a-three-year-program-what-should-the-program-manager-do-next&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 78. The program manager has a global program with five component projects. The program sponsor wants the management plans, processes/procedures, and technology to be uniform across the program. The requirements will create issues and result in increased costs. The program sponsor is new and has imposed these new requirements six months into a three-year program. What should the program manager do next?&lt;/h4&gt;
