&lt;h4 id=&#34;1-a-program-manager-prepares-the-program-for-review-to-secure-funding-by-senior-management-which-of-the-following-must-the-program-manager-identify-when-creating-the-program-charter&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#1-a-program-manager-prepares-the-program-for-review-to-secure-funding-by-senior-management-which-of-the-following-must-the-program-manager-identify-when-creating-the-program-charter&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 1. A program manager prepares the program for review to secure funding by senior management. Which of the following must the program manager identify when creating the program charter?&lt;/h4&gt;
