&lt;h4 id=&#34;2-an-rd-group-director-approves-a-major-programs-charter-although-the-director-has-a-high-level-of-understanding-of-the-programs-scope-they-are-unsure-of-how-the-program-manager-can-be-successful-in-delivering-the-programs-commitments-what-should-the-program-manager-do-to-align-stakeholders-with-planning-and-monitoring-the-programs-progress&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#2-an-rd-group-director-approves-a-major-programs-charter-although-the-director-has-a-high-level-of-understanding-of-the-programs-scope-they-are-unsure-of-how-the-program-manager-can-be-successful-in-delivering-the-programs-commitments-what-should-the-program-manager-do-to-align-stakeholders-with-planning-and-monitoring-the-programs-progress&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 2. An R&amp;amp;D group director approves a major program’s charter. Although the director has a high level of understanding of the program’s scope, they are unsure of how the program manager can be successful in delivering the program’s commitments. What should the program manager do to align stakeholders with planning and monitoring the program’s progress?&lt;/h4&gt;
